node.text:
“The land of the free and the home of the brave”
I always wondered “why did we migrate to the US?”
“Why didn’t we migrate to somewhere else, say Europe... like Italy?
I would’ve loved to speak Italian and pretty sure would’ve picked up English on the way”
Thinking back, it was the freedoms and opportunity this country provides.
Growing up in Iraq, we were forced to obey the government, we couldn’t say certain things, or even travel and see the world.
Being able to say, eat, act and become what I desire, has allowed me to achieve levels I would have never achieved where I come from.
Now yes, you may think, “well, America isn’t all sunshine and rainbows, politicians have gone mad and laws are stricter than ever” and you maybe right, but no one is perfect.
But, I can become whatever I desire. I can plan for the future. I can care for my family and loved ones!
With the opportunities this country has given my family and I, we will always be thankful.
With that said, I’d like to take this moment to remember all those who lost their lives and/or a loved one 20 years ago.
May this disastrous event be the last tragedy this country ever experiences and may all of us in America and around the world live in peace, love and prosperity!

If you want to get rich you’ll have to make sacrifices.

While others party, you work…

While others watch TV, you read and learn…

While others blow their money, you use your money to invest in your skills and knowledge.

It’s a sacrifice at first but it will pay off.

Because once you built your business and gained momentum…

You are able to live life on your terms.

Are you willing to make sacrifices now to gain freedom later?

If so…

node.text:
How billionaires and successful people start their day!

Isn’t it interesting how all of them get up at different times and do different things in their mornings?

When it comes to morning routines, there is no “one size fits all”...

"Poor" people can't afford "rich" people luxuries like $50,000 watches and such…

But they don't need to. I'd even say they shouldn't. 

Because they got a Iuxury rich people don't :

An abundance of time. 

Rich people have to sacrifice a lot before they are wealthy:

No Tv, No games, No sleeping in, No fixed work- end time, No free time with their families…

Poor people still can give time freely. 

If they used it to better themselves…

Grow their skills, learn from other people's mistakes...

You could have everything rich people have at half the sacrifice.

Here’s why those 5 really are making the rich richer:

If you wake up before everyone else, you can act before everyone else and no one will disturb you.

Before the others even started their day you already conquered yours.

“Let me think about this” is a broke person’s response. If you see an opportunity in front of you, take it. Fear isn’t making your rich- action is.
Spending money on status objects to flex is broke person behaviour. Rich people know they’re rich, they don’t need others to believe it, too. If you put most of your money into investments and pay for what you need with the returns, you’ll never worry about money again.

4. TV isn’t meant to make you rich. It’s meant to keep you broke and small because it’s wasting your time with pointless information, fear mongering news, and voyeuristic distractions like reality TV.

Reading gives you knowledge and knowledge is power- that was already true in medieval times. The rich could read, the poor could not. The rich were hosting games for the poor to watch instead of educating them. Think about that.

5. Meditation clears your mind and allows you to focus on success. Every day you’re bombarded with impressions- mediation beats overwhelm and makes sure you’re resistant against media manipulation.

So adopt those behaviors NOW, otherwise, it wouldn’t matter what you’re doing to become rich.

And when you’re ready to live a life with rich people habits, start something that’s gonna empower their lifestyle. Here’s how:

node.text:
THIS is the biggest difference between the rich and the poor.

Poor people try to play status games. They buy fancy things just to look rich.

They do this because they hope that others will admire them and their fancy lifestyle.

BUT…

Actual wealthy people don’t care about these things.

They don’t need the newest, fanciest car…

They often look very casual, live in a normal sized home, and eat at normal restaurants.

That’s because they don’t need to impress others.

Rich people focus on impact, not on admiration from others.

And probably the biggest difference of all…

Is how they think about money.

Poor people spend what they have just to look richer.

Whereas rich people invest their money to actually become and stay rich.

If you are just starting out on your journey to build wealth, the best investment you can make is to invest in yourself.

So, if you are ready to invest in your skills…

follow 👉@bjkuniversity
